## REPORTING SYSTEM

Delivery: end of last week of every month
Production: pull data → populate template → Claude generates commentary → review → publish
Total time: 20–30 minutes per client

Data sources:
- X: impressions, engagements, profile visits, follower growth, link clicks
- TikTok: views, watch time, average watch percentage, follower growth, profile visits
- LinkedIn: impressions, reactions, comments, follower growth, post clicks
- YouTube Shorts: views, watch time, retention rate, subscriber growth, impressions CTR

Report contents:
- Overview metrics: total views, followers gained, engagement rate, profile visits with MoM deltas
- Reach by platform
- Top performing video
- Strategic recommendation for next month

Claude commentary prompt:
You are a content strategist writing a monthly performance summary for a client report. Be direct, specific, and strategic. No fluff. Write like a senior analyst, not a marketer.

Client: [CLIENT NAME]
Product: [ONE LINE PRODUCT DESCRIPTION]
Month: [MONTH]

This month's data:
- Total views: [X] (vs last month: [X])
- Followers gained: [X]
- Engagement rate: [X%]
- Profile visits: [X]
- Top platform: [X] with [X] views
- Top video: [TITLE] — [X] views, [X%] engagement
- Top format: [FORMAT]
- Watch time / retention: [X]

Write:
1. A 2-sentence performance summary
2. One insight — why the top video performed
3. One specific recommendation for next month

Keep it under 150 words total. No bullet points. No headers.

End of month timeline:
- Day 25: pull all platform data
- Day 26: populate templates, run Claude prompt, personalise
- Day 27: publish all reports, send notification emails, begin next month strategy

